# Security Enhanced Linux

-- config file  /etc/sysconfig/selinux
-- config 	/etc/selinux/config  
#LOGS  /var/log/messages   # e.g. avc:denied message  


# Check Status

-- sestatus
OR 
-- getenforce

# Operation Modes

1. Enforcing
2. Permissive
3. Disabled

# Terminologies

AVC 		- Access Vector cache 	# This is where SELinux keeps its policies
Subject 	- This can be a process, program that needs to access a resource controlled by SELinux

# Types of Policies

1. Targeted policies - 
2. Multi-level Security (MLS)
